  <prompt>
    Update `docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md` with three new sections derived from Phase 4 findings:

    (a) **Ledger lifecycle** (per FR-07): document the real-bug-ledger state machine (`open` → `assigned-to-r2` → `in-progress` → `repaired`/`transferred-to-sibling`/`archived-as-dead-target` → `closed`). Cover: when to file vs when to fix, owner assignment rules, fix-by date logic, escalation paths. r2 is the canonical execution example to reference.

    (b) **TestClock + seeded-Guid pattern** (per FR-13): merge the pattern draft from Phase 4 Track C (task 042's output `notes/testclock-pattern-draft.md`) into the procedure doc. Cover: abstraction signature, DI registration, TestClock/TestGuidProvider test-side usage, when-to-use, r3 migration plan reference.

    (c) **Anti-drift effectiveness findings reference** (per FR-09): brief section pointing to `baseline/anti-drift-effectiveness-2026-08-XX.md` (Phase 4 Track E output). Include: high-level finding (compliance rate band); reference to corrective-action proposals if any. Does NOT inline-duplicate the report — references and cross-links.

    Per D-04, this is the governance update that captures Phase 4 findings; NOT full remediation. r3 (if commissioned) acts on the recommendations.

    Per CLAUDE.md §3, `docs/` is sub-agent-safe — this task does NOT need main-session-only treatment.
  </prompt>

  <role>Documentation AI agent updating the testing-and-code-quality procedure doc with Phase 4 outputs.</role>

