  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §5.6 / FR-07, the ledger lifecycle was operationalized in r1 + r2 but not yet documented as a reusable procedure. r2 close is the right moment to codify: r1 + r2 together demonstrate the full lifecycle (file → assigned → in-progress → repaired / transferred / archived → closed) with 20 ledger entries as worked examples.

      Per design.md §5.5 Track C / FR-13, the TestClock pattern documentation lives in `testing-and-code-quality.md` (NOT in `.claude/` — it's a development procedure, not a binding constraint). Task 042 drafts the pattern; this task merges it into the procedure doc.

      Per FR-09 / NFR-07, the anti-drift effectiveness report is the published evidence for D-05's design choice (no CI script). The procedure doc references the report so future contributors find the evidence base without searching project-internal `baseline/`.

      All three sections are ADDITIVE — existing procedure-doc structure is preserved. The doc has been the canonical reference since pre-r1; r2's contribution is the lifecycle codification + new patterns.
    </background>
